#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"B<sigaltstack>()  allows a thread to define a new alternate signal stack and/"
"or retrieve the state of an existing alternate signal stack.  An alternate "
"signal stack is used during the execution of a signal handler if the "
"establishment of that handler (see B<sigaction>(2))  requested it."
msgstr ""
"B<sigaltstack>() permet à un thread de définir une nouvelle pile spécifique "
"pour les gestionnaires de signaux et/ou de récupérer l'état d'une pile "
"spécifique de signal déjà existante. Une pile spécifique de signal est "
"utilisée durant l'exécution d'un gestionnaire de signal si la mise en place "
"de ce gestionnaire (consultez B<sigaction>(2)) le spécifiait."

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"The normal sequence of events for using an alternate signal stack is the "
"following:"
msgstr ""
"La séquence d'actions nominale pour utiliser une pile spécifique de signal "
"est la suivante\\ :"

#. type: TP
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "1."
msgstr "1."

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid "Allocate an area of memory to be used for the alternate signal stack."
msgstr ""
"Allouer une zone mémoire qui sera utilisée comme pile spécifique de signal."

#. type: TP
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "2."
msgstr "2."

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"Use B<sigaltstack>()  to inform the system of the existence and location of "
"the alternate signal stack."
msgstr ""
"Utiliser B<sigaltstack>() afin d'informer le système de l'existence et de la "
"position de la pile spécifique de signal."

#. type: TP
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "3."
msgstr "3."

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"When establishing a signal handler using B<sigaction>(2), inform the system "
"that the signal handler should be executed on the alternate signal stack by "
"specifying the B<SA_ONSTACK> flag."
msgstr ""
"Lors de la mise en place du gestionnaire de signal en utilisant "
"B<sigaction>(2), informer le système que ce gestionnaire de signal doit être "
"exécuté sur la pile spécifique de signal en positionnant le drapeau "
"B<SA_ONSTACK>."

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"The I<ss> argument is used to specify a new alternate signal stack, while "
"the I<old_ss> argument is used to retrieve information about the currently "
"established signal stack.  If we are interested in performing just one of "
"these tasks, then the other argument can be specified as NULL."
msgstr ""
"L'argument I<ss> est utilisé afin de définir une nouvelle pile spécifique de "
"signal, tandis que l'argument I<old_ss> est utilisé afin de récupérer des "
"informations sur la pile de signal actuellement en place. Si une seule de "
"ces actions vous intéresse, alors l'autre argument peut être positionné à "
"NULL."

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"The I<stack_t> type used to type the arguments of this function is defined "
"as follows:"
msgstr ""
"Le type I<stack_t> utilisé pour typer les paramètres de cette fonction est "
"défini comme suit :"

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid ""
"typedef struct {\n"
"    void  *ss_sp;     /* Base address of stack */\n"
"    int    ss_flags;  /* Flags */\n"
"    size_t ss_size;   /* Number of bytes in stack */\n"
"} stack_t;\n"
msgstr ""
"typedef struct {\n"
"    void  *ss_sp;     /* Adresse de base de la pile*/\n"
"    int    ss_flags;  /* Drapeaux */\n"
"    size_t ss_size;   /* Nombre d'octets dans la pile */\n"
"} stack_t;\n"

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"To establish a new alternate signal stack, the fields of this structure are "
"set as follows:"
msgstr ""
"Pour mettre en place une nouvelle pile de signal spécifique, les champs de "
"cette structure sont définis comme suit :"

#. type: TP
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "I<ss.ss_flags>"
msgstr "I<ss.ss_flags>"

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid "This field contains either 0, or the following flag:"
msgstr "Ce champ contient soit B<0>, soit le drapeau suivant :"

#. type: TP
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<SS_AUTODISARM> (since Linux 4.7)"
msgstr "B<SS_AUTODISARM> (depuis Linux 4.7)"

#.  commit 2a74213838104a41588d86fd5e8d344972891ace
#.  See tools/testing/selftests/sigaltstack/sas.c in kernel sources
#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"Clear the alternate signal stack settings on entry to the signal handler.  "
"When the signal handler returns, the previous alternate signal stack "
"settings are restored."
msgstr ""
"Effacer les paramètres de la pile de signal spécifique lors de l'entrée dans "
"le gestionnaire de signal. Au renvoi du gestionnaire de signal, les "
"paramètres de la pile de signal spécifique seront restaurés."

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"This flag was added in order to make it safe to switch away from the signal "
"handler with B<swapcontext>(3).  Without this flag, a subsequently handled "
"signal will corrupt the state of the switched-away signal handler.  On "
"kernels where this flag is not supported, B<sigaltstack>()  fails with the "
"error B<EINVAL> when this flag is supplied."
msgstr ""
"Ce drapeau a été ajouté afin de sécuriser la désactivation d'un gestionnaire "
"de signal avec B<swapcontext>(3). Sans ce drapeau, un signal géré après "
"cette désactivation corrompra l'état du gestionnaire de signal désactivé. "
"Sur les noyaux où ce drapeau n'est pas pris en charge, B<sigaltstack>() "
"échoue avec l'erreur B<EINVAL> quand ce drapeau est fourni."

#. type: TP
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "I<ss.ss_sp>"
msgstr "I<ss.ss_sp>"

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"This field specifies the starting address of the stack.  When a signal "
"handler is invoked on the alternate stack, the kernel automatically aligns "
"the address given in I<ss.ss_sp> to a suitable address boundary for the "
"underlying hardware architecture."
msgstr ""
"Ce champ indique l'adresse de début de la pile. Lorsqu'un gestionnaire de "
"signal est appelé sur la pile spécifique, le noyau aligne automatiquement "
"l'adresse donnée dans I<ss.ss_sp> sur une valeur correcte pour "
"l'architecture matérielle utilisée."

#. type: TP
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "I<ss.ss_size>"
msgstr "I<ss.ss_size>"

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"This field specifies the size of the stack.  The constant B<SIGSTKSZ> is "
"defined to be large enough to cover the usual size requirements for an "
"alternate signal stack, and the constant B<MINSIGSTKSZ> defines the minimum "
"size required to execute a signal handler."
msgstr ""
"Ce champ spécifie l'adresse de la pile. La constante B<SIGSTKSZ> est définie "
"de façon à être suffisamment grande pour couvrir les besoins typiques en "
"espace mémoire d'une pile spécifique de signal, et la constante "
"B<MINSIGSTKSZ> définit la taille minimale nécessaire à l'exécution d'un "
"gestionnaire de signal."

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"To disable an existing stack, specify I<ss.ss_flags> as B<SS_DISABLE>.  In "
"this case, the kernel ignores any other flags in I<ss.ss_flags> and the "
"remaining fields in I<ss>."
msgstr ""
"Afin de désactiver une pile existante, positionnez I<ss.ss_flags> à "
"B<SS_DISABLE>. Dans ce cas, le noyau ignore tous les autres drapeaux de I<ss."
"ss_flags> et les autres champs de I<ss>."

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"If I<old_ss> is not NULL, then it is used to return information about the "
"alternate signal stack which was in effect prior to the call to "
"B<sigaltstack>().  The I<old_ss.ss_sp> and I<old_ss.ss_size> fields return "
"the starting address and size of that stack.  The I<old_ss.ss_flags> may "
"return either of the following values:"
msgstr ""
"Si I<old_ss> ne vaut pas NULL, alors il est utilisé afin de renvoyer des "
"informations sur la pile spécifique de signal qui était utilisée avant "
"l'appel à B<sigaltstack>(). Les champs I<old_ss.ss_sp> et I<old_ss.ss_size> "
"renvoient l'adresse de départ et la taille de cette pile. Le champ I<old_ss."
"ss_flags> peut renvoyer l'une des valeurs suivantes\\ :"

#. type: TP
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<SS_ONSTACK>"
msgstr "B<SS_ONSTACK>"

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"The thread is currently executing on the alternate signal stack.  (Note that "
"it is not possible to change the alternate signal stack if the thread is "
"currently executing on it.)"
msgstr ""
"Le thread s'exécute actuellement sur la pile spécifique de signal. "
"(Remarquez qu'il n'est pas possible de changer la pile spécifique de signal "
"si le thread est en train de s'exécuter sur cette dernière.)"

#. type: TP
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<SS_DISABLE>"
msgstr "B<SS_DISABLE>"

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid "The alternate signal stack is currently disabled."
msgstr "La pile spécifique de signal est actuellement désactivée."

#.  FIXME Was it intended that one can set up a different alternative
#.  signal stack in this scenario? (In passing, if one does this, the
#.  sigaltstack(NULL, &old_ss) now returns old_ss.ss_flags==SS_AUTODISARM
#.  rather than old_ss.ss_flags==SS_DISABLE. The API design here seems
#.  confusing...
#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"Alternatively, this value is returned if the thread is currently executing "
"on an alternate signal stack that was established using the B<SS_AUTODISARM> "
"flag.  In this case, it is safe to switch away from the signal handler with "
"B<swapcontext>(3).  It is also possible to set up a different alternative "
"signal stack using a further call to B<sigaltstack>()."
msgstr ""
"Sinon, cette valeur est renvoyée si le processus s'exécute actuellement sur "
"une pile de signal spécifique mise en place en utilisant le drapeau "
"B<SS_AUTODISARM>. Dans ce cas, il est plus sûr de désactiver le gestionnaire "
"de signal avec B<swapcontext>(3). Il est également possible de définir une "
"autre pile spécifique en utilisant un autre appel B<sigaltstack>()."

#. type: TP
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<SS_AUTODISARM>"
msgstr "B<SS_AUTODISARM>"

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"The alternate signal stack has been marked to be autodisarmed as described "
"above."
msgstr ""
"La pile spécifique de signal a été marquée pour être désactivée comme décrit "
"ci-dessus."

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"By specifying I<ss> as NULL, and I<old_ss> as a non-NULL value, one can "
"obtain the current settings for the alternate signal stack without changing "
"them."
msgstr ""
"En positionnant I<ss> sur NULL et I<old_ss> sur une valeur autre que NULL, "
"on peut obtenir les paramètres de la pile de signal spécifique sans les "
"modifier."

#. type: SH
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "RETURN VALUE"
msgstr "VALEUR RENVOYÉE"

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"B<sigaltstack>()  returns 0 on success, or -1 on failure with I<errno> set "
"to indicate the error."
msgstr ""
"B<sigaltstack>() renvoie B<0> en cas de succès, ou B<-1> en cas d'échec en "
"positionnant alors I<errno> pour préciser l'erreur."

#. type: SH
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: mageia-cauldron opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "ERRORS"
msgstr "ERREURS"

#. type: TP
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<EFAULT>"
msgstr "B<EFAULT>"

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"Either I<ss> or I<old_ss> is not NULL and points to an area outside of the "
"process's address space."
msgstr ""
"Un des paramètres I<ss> ou I<old_ss> ne vaut pas NULL et pointe vers une "
"zone mémoire n'appartenant pas à l'espace d'adressage du processus."

#. type: TP
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<EINVAL>"
msgstr "B<EINVAL>"

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid "I<ss> is not NULL and the I<ss_flags> field contains an invalid flag."
msgstr ""
"I<ss> ne vaut pas NULL et le champ I<ss_flags> contient une valeur non "
"valable."

#. type: TP
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<ENOMEM>"
msgstr "B<ENOMEM>"

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"The specified size of the new alternate signal stack I<ss.ss_size> was less "
"than B<MINSIGSTKSZ>."
msgstr ""
"La taille de la nouvelle pile spécifique de signal indiquée (I<ss.ss_size>) "
"est inférieure à B<MINSIGSTKSZ>."

#. type: TP
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-leap-15-5 opensuse-tumbleweed
#, no-wrap
msgid "B<EPERM>"
msgstr "B<EPERM>"

#. type: Plain text
#: archlinux debian-bullseye debian-unstable fedora-37 fedora-rawhide
#: opensuse-tumbleweed
msgid ""
"An attempt was made to change the alternate signal stack while it was active "
"(i.e., the thread was already executing on the current alternate signal "
"stack)."
msgstr ""
"On a essayé de modifier la pile spécifique de signal alors que celle-ci "
"était active (c'est-à-dire, le thread était déjà en train de s'exécuter sur "
"la pile spécifique de signal courante)."

